{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 21:26:15.437340", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Detected anomaly: End-to-end data-plane connectivity is down across the fabric. Even same-leaf, same-subnet hosts cannot reach each other.\\n- Localization: The issue is centralized in the SDN control plane. All OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are configured to connect to the controller at tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 but are not connected. Management IP connectivity is fine, so this is not a basic IP reachability problem.\\n- Root cause: Controller connectivity/port mismatch. The controller at 20.0.0.100 is not listening on TCP 6633 (OpenFlow legacy port), while it appears reachable on TCP 6653 (OpenFlow 1.3 default). With fail_mode=secure and no controller connection, the switches install no flows, causing all traffic to be dropped.\\n\\nKey Findings and Evidence\\n\\n1) Host dataplane symptoms\\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2 (same leaf, 10.0.0.0/24): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable” reported by 10.0.0.1.\\n  Evidence:\\n  PING 10.0.0.2 from host_1_1:\\n  - 3 packets transmitted, 0 received, +3 errors, 100% packet loss\\n- Host interfaces are up and correctly configured in 10.0.0.0/24:\\n  - host_1_1: 10.0.0.1/24, route: 10.0.0.0/24 dev eth0\\n  - host_1_2: 10.0.0.2/24, route: 10.0.0.0/24 dev eth0\\n\\n2) OVS switch state\\n- All switches are configured with a controller:\\n  - leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\", fail_mode: secure\\n- All three switches are not connected to the controller:\\n  - ovs-vsctl list Controller shows:\\n    - is_connected: false\\n    - status: state=CONNECTING, last_error=\"Connection timed out\"\\n- No OpenFlow rules installed on any switch:\\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1 shows empty flow tables\\n- Physical/port state appears healthy:\\n  - ovs-ofctl show reports all data-plane ports to hosts/spine are LIVE, 10GB-FD COPPER\\n  - Interfaces toward hosts and fabric are UP at the Linux level\\n\\n3) Management network health\\n- Switch management interfaces are up with correct IPs:\\n  - leaf_1: 20.0.0.3/24\\n  - leaf_2: 20.0.0.4/24\\n  - spine_1: 20.0.0.1/24\\n- L3 connectivity on management network is good:\\n  - leaf_1 -> 20.0.0.1: OK\\n  - leaf_1 -> 20.0.0.100: OK\\n  - leaf_2 -> 20.0.0.1: OK\\n  - spine_1 -> 20.0.0.3: OK\\n  This confirms IP reachability to the controller IP (20.0.0.100) from the switches.\\n\\n4) Controller port tests\\n- TCP reachability tests from switches to controller:\\n  - leaf_1 -> 20.0.0.100:6633: fail (RC=1)\\n  - leaf_1 -> 20.0.0.100:6653: success (RC=0)\\n  - leaf_2 -> 20.0.0.100:6633: fail (RC=1)\\n  - spine_1 -> 20.0.0.100:6633: fail (RC=1)\\n- Interpretation: The controller host is reachable at IP level, but the OpenFlow service is not listening on 6633. Port 6653 appears open on 20.0.0.100.\\n\\nAnomaly Assessment\\n- Abnormal behavior: End-to-end traffic is blackholed despite healthy physical links. Absence of flows on all OVS bridges combined with fail_mode=secure explains the observed drop of even local L2 traffic.\\n- Scope: Entire fabric is affected because all switches rely on the same controller and share the same (incorrect) controller port configuration.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Not a per-link or per-interface failure: ports are LIVE/UP with no errors.\\n- Centralized control-plane issue:\\n  - Either the controller process is not listening on 6633, or\\n  - The switches are misconfigured to use 6633 while the controller expects 6653.\\n- Affected devices: All three OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) and the controller endpoint 20.0.0.100 (service/port configuration).\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Controller connectivity mismatch: OVS set to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 while the controller is likely serving on port 6653. In fail_mode=secure with no active controller session, OpenFlow tables are empty and all traffic is dropped.\\n\\nImpact\\n- Complete data-plane outage for hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 across the fabric, including intra-leaf connectivity, because no L2/L3 forwarding entries are programmed. Management network remains unaffected., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='455c2c66-bd47-4657-ac48-cf082f40a5b8'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
